Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Cook Pasta Roni according to directions on box using water and milk. When pasta is done, stir in beaten eggs and place into a greased 9 inch pie pan and form a shell with pasta (like a pie shell). Mix together alfredo sauce, chicken, bacon bits and parmesan cheese. Pour mixture into pasta shell and bake for 15 minutes. Top with chopped tomato.